He was willing to come into this world, to go to the cross, to settle the sin question.

59
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:47,200
Now the cross is before him, only hours away.

60
00:09:48,880 --> 00:10:11,680
Soon he will be hanging on that tree in the sinner's rightful place, bearing the sinner's judgment, bearing our penalty, bearing our sin, and yet he looks on it in perfect confidence because he knows that he cannot be held by death.

61
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:19,120
He is looking on it onto the resurrection through which he would receive glorification and would glorify the Father.

62
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:32,080
From verse 1, we have here the glory of our Lord presented in the distinct ways, two distinct ways, his essential glory and his acquired glory.

63
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:40,080
In this first verse, when he says, Glorify thy Son, that thy son may also glorify thee, we have the acquired glory.

64
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:48,240
In verse 5, he says, O Father, glorify me with thine own self, with the glory which I had with thee before the world was.

65
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:51,040
Here he speaks of his essential glory.

66
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:56,560
You see, he was one with the Father from eternity.

67
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:12,160
Yet in infinite grace, he laid aside the outward signs of glory, and he came into this world as a stranger and a pilgrim in identifying himself with mankind, yet without sin.

68
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:23,040
Now he is going back from whence he came, and all that has been hidden will be fully manifest, his essential glory as one with the Father.

69
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:29,120
How does verse 1 speak of the glory our Lord acquired?

70
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:35,120
He does it by his coming into the world and doing his work down here.

71
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:42,960
First of all, only through the cross was he able to receive the glory of Saviorhood.

72
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:47,360
Otherwise, he could have never been a savior.

73
00:11:48,720 --> 00:12:05,040
In Hebrews, we read he was made perfect through suffering, not as the character, for he was always perfect in character, but without his sacrificial death, he could have never been the captain of our salvation.

74
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:09,680
The suffering Savior brought our salvation free.

75
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:15,360
Secondly, we have his glory as head of the church.

76
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,440
He was always the head of creation.

77
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:21,760
In Colossians, we read that he brought everything into existence.

78
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:29,440
It is in the resurrection that he is the firstborn among the dead and that he becomes the head of the church.

79
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:39,520
Thirdly, there is his glory as the coming king who will reign over Israel and over all the people to the ends of the earth.

80
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:46,320
And of course, this was dependent on his obedience to the Father's will down here from the manger to the cross.

81
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:52,160
And in view of this, he is the proclaimed Jehovah's King over all the earth.

82
00:12:52,480 --> 00:13:01,920
