114
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,840
Oh, how he loves you.

115
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,800
Oh, how he loves me and you.

116
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:33,040
In the mind of God, long before this world began, he gave every individual who would believe on his son to Christ for all eternity.

117
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:39,120
Our blessed Lord gives eternal life to as many as the Father has given him.

118
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:41,840
How many does he give to the Lord?

119
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:44,160
All who will come to him.

120
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:51,360
All that the Father giveth me shall come to me, and him that cometh to me, Jesus said, I will in no wise cast out.

121
00:16:52,800 --> 00:17:00,640
If you have not received Christ as your Savior, your Lord today, and you want to receive him, then come.

122
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,560
He will not cast you out.

123
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:10,800
Then when you have come to him, you can say, I am one of those whom the Father has given to the Son.

124
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,680
What a blessed consolation.

125
00:17:14,320 --> 00:17:17,360
We belong to Jesus if you trust him.

126
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:29,040
From verse 3 we read, And this is eternal life, that they might know thee, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom thou hast sent.

127
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:32,400
This verse gives us the manifestation.

128
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:37,120
It shows us clearly eternal life.

129
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:44,000
That they might know thee, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom thou hast sent.

130
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,280
What does this mean?

131
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:48,720
It means we cannot know God the Father.

132
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:54,720
We cannot know God the Son apart from having eternal life.

133
00:17:55,600 --> 00:18:01,280
Jesus says, Jesus gave men eternal life while he was here.

134
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:07,200
And he gives men eternal life still by enabling them to know God.

135
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:12,640
So whoever knows God through Christ is in possession of eternal life.

136
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:16,160
And if you don't know God, my friend, you cannot enter.

137
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,120
There is no other way under God's heaven.

138
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:25,120
Neither is there any name under heaven given among men whereby we might be saved.

139
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,640
Jesus said, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

140
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:31,600
And no man comes to the Father but by me.

141
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,520
It's not by good works.

142
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:37,680
It's not by all our good doings and our goodness and kindness.

143
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:43,040
And all these things are great and important, but my friend, they will send you to hell.

144
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:48,000
Get there by knowing the Father.

145
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,680
To know him is to know I can hear you.

146
00:18:56,240 --> 00:19:00,720
In the fourth verse, our Savior presents two things that we must make note of.

147
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:08,640
Let us read his glorious words that he speaks to the Father, and he said, I have glorified thee on the earth.

148
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:12,560
I have finished the work which thou gavest me to do.

149
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:20,800
First of all, our Lord goes back over his journey here on this earth and he says, Father, I've glorified thee on the earth.

150
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,520
He had not one regret.

151
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:37,840
There are things in the world today that would doubtless, no doubt, that would, those who would deny the deity of our Lord, but all they need to do is to think back on Christ's record.

152
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:43,600
He lived down here on this earth, and he never had one regret.

153
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:48,320
He never said one word that he had to apologize for.

154
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:53,920
He never did one thing that he wished later he had not said or done.

155
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,480
He never made one mistake.

156
00:19:56,800 --> 00:20:04,000
He never stumbled once on all the rocky path he tread from the manger of Bethlehem to the cross of Calvary.

157
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:07,360
How different from ourselves.

158
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:11,680
How could anyone challenge his deity?

159
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:16,960
How many can the world name who is free from all sin?

160
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,200
None, my friend, none.

161
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:23,680
Only he whom God sent from heaven knew no sin.

162
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,560
And Jesus knew he had not sinned.

163
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:31,840
And looking back over his life, he said, Father, I have glorified thee on earth.

164
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:36,640
In everything he said and did, he had the Father's glory.

165
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,520
We notice the second thing.

166
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:43,520
I have finished the work thou gavest me to do.

167
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:49,520
He said, Father, I've shown to the world the great loving heart.

168
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,800
Father, you are God.

169
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,760
I've glorified you on earth.

170
00:20:56,080 --> 00:21:01,120
I've made manifest to the world my Father in heaven.

171
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:05,120
He said, I have finished the work that I gave you to do.

172
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:10,080
Here you see, he has left us an example that we should follow in his steps.

173
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:20,720
In John chapter 2 and verse 6, we're told, he that saith, he abideth in him, ought himself also so to walk even as he walks.

174
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:25,040
Oh, you know, we can never walk perfectly as he walks.

175
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:27,280
We are full of failure.

176
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:32,240
But we can at least follow in his steps and seek to walk as he walks.

177
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:39,360
We read of the Apostle Paul who said, nearing the closing days of his ministry, he said, I have finished my course.

178
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:43,680
I have fought the good fight, and now I am ready to be offered.

179
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:56,720
Although Paul, who would be the first to admit it, failed many times, yet he followed in the Savior's steps and he glorified the Lord and he said he could gladly say, I have finished my course.

180
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:07,520
And we say that, my friends, when we come to light in it, and we stand before God, can we say, I have finished my course?

181
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:13,600
And said with joy unspeakable, I have finished my course.

182
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:20,160
We notice the order in which our Lord spoke these words.

183
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:23,920
First he said, I have glorified thee on earth.

184
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,880
I have finished the work thou gavest me to do.

185
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:30,880
First of all, he had before him the glory of God.

186
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:34,720
And then the work that was committed to him.

187
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:38,800
As we follow in his steps, there's something more important than working.

188
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,920
The glory of God comes before working.

189
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:49,760
You know, oftentimes when one is converted, we say, put him to work, give him something to do, but what happens?

190
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:54,320
Some people do things they are not prepared to do.

191
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:57,680
And work becomes a legality.

192
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:02,800
They are put to work before they know the blessedness and fullness of grace.

193
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:07,920
And they have no chance to see if God is glorified first of all in their life.

194
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:12,080
Or to see if he is foremost in their heart.

195
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:17,360
Or to see if his will is the first concern of their mind.

196
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:21,600
Oh my, how we need to get our priorities right.

197
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:27,040
Do we know if God is being glorified in our lives?

198
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:29,200
Is he the first in our hearts?

199
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:30,800
Is he first in our life?

200
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,360
Is he first in our giving?

201
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:35,920
Is he first in our talents?

202
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:42,960
Do we realize that he is the owner of our lives and that all that we are belongs to him?

203
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,200
Is he first?

204
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:48,160
Does he have priority in our lives?

205
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:56,080
You know, it's more important that God be glorified than that I accomplish certain things in the line of service.

206
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:03,840
You know, some invalids often bring more glory to God than he who can move around so easily.

207
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:12,400
The story is told of a dear mother and her daughter who lived in a tenement house set back off in the street, from a back street.

208
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:20,160
And the daughter, a young woman of perhaps 32, cared for her, her mother, dear mother, who sat in a child's high chair.

209
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,440
And she'd been afflicted with entire paralysis.

210
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:31,120
And for many years before, and for 22 years, that had been her throne, this little high chair.

