We might think of servants simply as those who are aided to the rich and to the distinguished.

429
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:43,920
But let us realize that the word servant doesn't necessarily mean a place of lowly degree.

430
00:57:44,560 --> 00:57:46,560
There are different kinds of servants.

431
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:52,640
There are the servants of the land who till the soil and grows the food for the rich and the poor alike.

432
00:57:53,120 --> 00:57:55,360
There are the servants of war who carry honors.

433
00:57:56,000 --> 00:58:00,800
There are servants of our country still whom we can uphold and honor.

434
00:58:01,120 --> 00:58:03,600
Then there are servants of the Lord Jesus Christ.

435
00:58:03,920 --> 00:58:10,160
And what greater honorable position could one have than just to be numbered among his servants?

436
00:58:10,480 --> 00:58:13,840
Jehaza was the servant of Elisha.

437
00:58:14,480 --> 00:58:17,440
Surely this was a privilege in itself.

438
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:18,480
Why?

439
00:58:19,040 --> 00:58:22,960
Just to be associated to such a man of God.

440
00:58:23,280 --> 00:58:39,760
Gehazah was the man by the side of Elisha to aid in the great and wonderful task of a prophet like Elisha himself, who was the attendant and disciple of Elijah and who received the mantle that fell from his shoulders.

441
00:58:40,080 --> 00:58:45,360
Even so Gehazah was one in a position for spiritual enrichment.

442
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:54,720
Did you know that it is interesting to realize that the name Gehazah means a valley of vision, a valley of vision.

443
00:58:54,960 --> 00:59:10,560
His name so very fitly represents his honorable position because many a vision of the power and the goodness of God did he get through the acts and the words of Elisha, his divinely appointed master.

444
00:59:10,880 --> 00:59:26,640
But alas, but alas, although Gehazel lived and moved in a spiritual environment, a spiritual atmosphere, yet it seemed to me with all the pride and self-importance of an unconverted officer in the church.

445
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:35,920
Someone has said that spiritual influences and opportunities has about as little effect on some souls as the sunshine has on the toast.

446
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:39,280
And how very true that is.

447
00:59:39,760 --> 00:59:47,040
There are those who can sit for years under the gospel ministry and yet be nothing the better of it in the end.

448
00:59:47,360 --> 00:59:55,280
Jehaza, a man with such a special privilege, with such an opportunity, gained nothing at all.

449
00:59:58,480 --> 01:00:03,280
But we find he was a man with a selfishness.

450
01:00:03,920 --> 01:00:12,560
Let us notice the words of verse 20 in our text, especially the last part of the verse of 2 Kings chapter 5, verse 20.

451
01:00:12,880 --> 01:00:23,600
But Gehazah, the servant of Elisha, the man of God, said, Behold, my master hath spared Naaman the Syrian in not receiving at his hand that which he brought.

452
01:00:24,160 --> 01:00:29,280
But as the Lord liveth, I will run after him, and I will take somewhat of him.

453
01:00:31,440 --> 01:00:36,480
No doubt the temptation was exceptionally great to a covetous man.

454
01:00:36,800 --> 01:00:47,040
And as we take a general look at Jehazah, simply from the reading of this verse 20, we immediately see that he is a greedy, selfish, covetous person.

455
01:00:47,680 --> 01:01:01,840
Here we see, here he sees an unprecedented opportunity, he thought, of making himself rich without robbing his master just by inventing a seemingly honest story to tell Naaman.

456
01:01:02,400 --> 01:01:07,840
Jehazah said, I will run after Naaman, the Syrian, and take somewhat of him.

457
01:01:08,160 --> 01:01:19,200
But you see, this I will, this I will of his was an act of rebellion against the spirit and the honor of his master Elisha and of his God.

458
01:01:19,840 --> 01:01:31,280
For a few moments, as Jehazah thought on this strategy of this scheme, certainly there was that battle of good and evil fought within his soul.

459
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:40,880
Surely he knew that his master Elisha had turned down the gifts of Maaman that God might be glorified, that God might be honored.

460
01:01:41,040 --> 01:01:51,680
But nevertheless, Jehazah's selfish love and covetous desire for material, temporal things caused him to surrender his will to do this evil thing.

461
01:01:52,000 --> 01:02:05,120
And in so doing, in making such a decision, he revealed a sinful distrust in God and a desire to take the province of God in his own hands to do his own thing.

462
01:02:06,080 --> 01:02:10,080
The Bible tells us that the love of money is the root of all evil.

463
01:02:10,240 --> 01:02:12,640
No, it didn't say that money is the root of all evil.

464
01:02:12,960 --> 01:02:15,200
But the love of money is the root of all evil.

465
01:02:15,360 --> 01:02:19,040
Gehazah here completely reveals his first love.

466
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:22,480
It was for himself and his own self-interest.

467
01:02:23,040 --> 01:02:28,480
It was for his own selfish pleas, for fame, and recognition, and power.

468
01:02:30,320 --> 01:02:31,840
Isn't that so true in our world today?

469
01:02:32,800 --> 01:02:33,920
People want power.

470
01:02:34,160 --> 01:02:34,960
They want gain.

471
01:02:35,040 --> 01:02:35,840
They want fame.

472
01:02:37,920 --> 01:02:41,360
But they heat to themselves destruction.

473
01:02:42,640 --> 01:02:45,760
In the third place, let us mark the deceitful work of this man.

474
01:02:46,000 --> 01:02:48,800
Notice with me, verse 21 and 22.

475
01:02:49,120 --> 01:02:57,200
And we read here, So Gehazah followed after Naaman, and when Naaman saw him running after him, he alighted from the carriage to meet him and said, Is it all well?

476
01:02:57,680 --> 01:02:58,800
And he said, All is well.

477
01:02:58,960 --> 01:03:06,720
My master has sent me, saying, Behold, even now there come to me from Mount Ephraim two young men of the sons of the prophets.

478
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:11,600
Give them, I pray thee, a talent of silver and two changes of gold.

479
01:03:14,080 --> 01:03:22,640
As soon as his mind was made up to do this main cowardly deed, he goes into it with all earnestness.

480
01:03:23,120 --> 01:03:25,040
He has it all planned out.

481
01:03:25,360 --> 01:03:37,680
So he runs after David and he begins this lying tale that his master had sent him to plead for help for two young men of the sons of the prophet that had come to him in need.

482
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:47,280
We notice that after his heart was sowed on this evil task, the first utterance he made was a lie against his master.

483
01:03:48,480 --> 01:03:57,760
This evil story of Gehazah was not only proving him a liar, but it was also bringing reproach and grief upon his master.

484
01:03:58,080 --> 01:04:08,320
Dear friend, if you are a believer in Jesus Christ, no servant of Christ can act falsely without bringing grief to his master's heart.

485
01:04:08,640 --> 01:04:15,280
Oh, how it must have grieved the Savior's heart the night that Peter denied him there by the enemy's fire.

486
01:04:15,920 --> 01:04:19,440
It was the love of money that stowed away the heart of Gehazah.

487
01:04:19,600 --> 01:04:29,840
It has been said, as soon as the love of money strikes its roots into the heart, covetousness and falsehood must appear in the light as seen by God.

488
01:04:30,160 --> 01:04:35,520
Beloved heart, Satan is no different today than he was in the time of Gehazah.

489
01:04:35,840 --> 01:04:50,560
It is still his desired hope to fill our hearts with covetousness, with self-gain and greed, and to trick us to some cowardly lying scheme, even unto some act of pride.

490
01:04:51,120 --> 01:04:53,040
Let us be on our guard, folks.

491
01:04:53,360 --> 01:04:54,400
Let us be on our guard.

492
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:59,840
The Epistle James tells us, resist the devil, and he will flee from you.

493
01:05:00,400 --> 01:05:05,360
The fourth thing we should notice this morning is the singing success of Gehazah.

494
01:05:05,680 --> 01:05:12,880
We're aware of the fact and of the greed of Gehaza and his plan was to get for himself the silver and the garment.

495
01:05:13,200 --> 01:05:22,800
But even he himself was no doubt surprised that the silver and the garment succeeded beyond his expectation.

496
01:05:23,360 --> 01:05:31,120
Oh, isn't it that's normal and natural that the old devil is one who changes himself in the leaves of life?

497
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:37,360
And then if the devil had you already, he just makes things look better.

498
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:40,560
And boy, you just like, look how you are professing.

499
01:05:41,520 --> 01:05:43,760
Look how you're doing, how great it is.

500
01:05:46,560 --> 01:05:51,920
See, instead of him gathering one talent of silver, verse 23 tells us that he got two.

501
01:05:52,160 --> 01:05:57,360
And moreover, Naaman sent two of his servants to carry the goods back to Gehabah's house.

502
01:05:58,240 --> 01:06:00,880
How very fortunate this same thing for Gehavah.

503
01:06:01,200 --> 01:06:03,280
But how truly fortunate was it?

504
01:06:03,840 --> 01:06:12,080
What were his thoughts as he walked behind those servants of Naaman who were carrying the bags and garments all for his own use?

505
01:06:12,720 --> 01:06:17,360
He might have been thinking, does it mean it pay to be a hypocrite?

506
01:06:19,360 --> 01:06:25,600
Will these bags of silver or garments of beauty sufficiently compensate for a vile conscience?

507
01:06:26,800 --> 01:06:36,000
Well, whatever the thoughts may have been of Gehazer, we don't really know, but he must have been uneasy, far from contentment, far from peace.

508
01:06:36,720 --> 01:06:50,480
During the rich man of Luke chapter 16 knew what it was to be clothed in purple and robes and fare sumptuously every day while Lazarus sat in his gate full of swords.

509
01:06:51,120 --> 01:07:02,480
But as we read farther on and we see this rich man's final end, we are aware that to be clothed in purple robes and to fare sumptuously every day is by no means the kingdom of God.

510
01:07:03,440 --> 01:07:08,320
When we look at this man, we realize what the Bible says concerning the kingdom of God.

511
01:07:08,560 --> 01:07:14,000
It says that it is righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Ghost.

512
01:07:14,960 --> 01:07:16,560
And we think of Lazarus.

513
01:07:17,200 --> 01:07:21,040
Lazarus the beggar, he knew what it was to have deceived.

514
01:07:21,920 --> 01:07:26,400
But the rich man didn't, though he had had much riches.

515
01:07:27,920 --> 01:07:36,480
Neither could Jehazah, the selfish, covetous, envious worker of deceit, know joy and peace.

516
01:07:37,120 --> 01:07:42,080
Even though he had experienced a seemingly greater success than he expected.

517
01:07:42,960 --> 01:07:57,840
In the book of Psalms, chapter 73, Asiph said, I was envious when I saw the prosperity of the wicked until I went into the sanctuary of God, then understood I therein.

518
01:07:59,040 --> 01:08:01,520
Oh, my friends, have you ever just thanked God for your father?

519
01:08:02,720 --> 01:08:08,960
Have you ever thanked God that he set you where you are instead of rolling with all kinds of money?

520
01:08:10,960 --> 01:08:15,280
This reminds me that whenever I am weak, as Paul said, then am I strong?

521
01:08:17,440 --> 01:08:25,680
That God has kept me as I am, not one of wealth, but one that is concerned, realizing in my helplessness that God was a while money.

522
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:29,680
And it keeps me close to God because I fall on money.

523
01:08:31,440 --> 01:08:32,560
That's what God wants.

524
01:08:33,680 --> 01:08:38,000
That's why perhaps God teaches us without a lot of money, folks.

525
01:08:38,640 --> 01:08:39,200
His people.

526
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:44,320
Because whenever we get a lot of money, we start to make a den in the world.

527
01:08:44,480 --> 01:08:45,920
We become proud.

528
01:08:46,560 --> 01:08:48,160
And we lose sight of God.

529
01:08:48,720 --> 01:08:50,080
That's what Yehazim did.

530
01:08:50,240 --> 01:08:51,680
He lost sight of God.

531
01:08:52,240 --> 01:08:59,040
And he's like, in the case of this man Gehazman, the question is, will the eternal end justify the means?

532
01:08:59,200 --> 01:09:02,800
Will success atone for sin?

533
01:09:03,360 --> 01:09:04,880
The answer is a sad no.

534
01:09:05,200 --> 01:09:08,640
Sin will be found out and sin will be punished.

535
01:09:08,960 --> 01:09:11,280
This leads up to the fifth point of this message today.

536
01:09:11,520 --> 01:09:13,920
Let's mark Gehazah's unexpected discovery.

537
01:09:14,240 --> 01:09:16,080
Look at chapter 8, verse 25.

538
01:09:16,400 --> 01:09:18,000
Verse 25 is what it says.

539
01:09:18,320 --> 01:09:25,120
But he went in and stood before his master, and Elisha said unto him, From where comest thou, Gehaza?

540
01:09:25,360 --> 01:09:28,240
And he said, thy servant went not here or there.

541
01:09:29,280 --> 01:09:31,440
What do we see here, Gehazah, doing?

542
01:09:32,400 --> 01:09:36,640
We see him as he tries to rule the world if he's not divided.

543
01:09:37,520 --> 01:09:46,480
He went in and he stood before his master as he had done before, just as nothing had happened to mar their fellowship and his henry service.

544
01:09:47,040 --> 01:09:52,480
And inside his heart, certainly, Gehaza knew that he was guilty.

545
01:09:52,800 --> 01:09:59,600
He knew that he would not, that he would not admit it outwardly, you see, but his conscience, you see, was clear.

546
01:10:00,800 --> 01:10:05,600
He simply wanted to maintain his good standing before his master.

547
01:10:05,920 --> 01:10:10,080
So the first thing he did, he went in, took stand before his master.

548
01:10:10,400 --> 01:10:26,640
And thinking that his guilt was not showing, let us ask ourselves, have we ever been guilty of this same thing in seeking to maintain our standing before our heavenly master while there is unconfessed sin in the heart?

549
01:10:27,600 --> 01:10:31,040
And we know it, but some way or another we can justify it.

550
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:34,080
And Lord, I do thank you for you all.

551
01:10:34,880 --> 01:10:36,480
And we justify ourselves.

552
01:10:36,720 --> 01:10:38,320
There's a scripture for this.

553
01:10:38,640 --> 01:10:40,480
The Bible says, be not deceived.

554
01:10:40,640 --> 01:10:41,840
God is not false.

555
01:10:42,240 --> 01:10:46,720
Be sure your sin will find you out, rendering you unfit for service.

556
01:10:46,800 --> 01:10:50,320
Gehaza thought his sin was concealed.

557
01:10:50,960 --> 01:10:54,480
But Elisha said unto him, From where comest thou?

558
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:58,000
And Gehazah said, thy servant went not here or there.

559
01:10:58,560 --> 01:11:04,640
There was a bold lie here that Gehazah made, and Elisha knew it.

560
01:11:04,960 --> 01:11:12,800
But Gehazah took that fatal refuge of all backsliders, and he made an attempt at self-justification.

561
01:11:13,520 --> 01:11:15,200
He tried to hide his sin.

562
01:11:15,840 --> 01:11:26,560
But the Bible tells us in Proverbs 28, 13, he that coveth his sin shall not prosper, but whosoever confesseth and forsaketh them shall have mercy.

563
01:11:26,880 --> 01:11:40,080
The words of Elisha in verse 26, Let the shock Jehazah to his wits in all the selfish pride, must have withered away when he heard the prophet speak, went not my heart to thee.

564
01:11:42,000 --> 01:11:44,800
And then he goes on to say, is it a time to receive money?

565
01:11:45,600 --> 01:11:54,320
Is it a time to receive garments, olive yards, and vineyards, and sheep and oxen, and men's servants and maidservants?

566
01:11:54,960 --> 01:12:01,040
Elisha had spiritual perception, and he knew his servant was lying.

567
01:12:01,520 --> 01:12:06,480
Gehazah's secret sin was naked and bare before the eyes of his master.

568
01:12:06,800 --> 01:12:11,040
The real truth was revealed, and guilt was written all over Gehazah's face.

569
01:12:11,360 --> 01:12:12,880
There was no way to cover it up.

570
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:21,120
Oh, dear Christian friends, does not the heart of our Lord, does not the heart of our master always go with us?

571
01:12:22,000 --> 01:12:25,120
If we're a child of God, then what the Lord go with us?

572
01:12:25,360 --> 01:12:26,160
Praise His sin.

573
01:12:26,960 --> 01:12:28,560
Is this heart with us?

574
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:37,040
One day must we not stand before Him too to give an account of the deeds done in the body?

575
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:42,880
At that day, when we stand before Him, every secret sin will be revealed.

576
01:12:43,200 --> 01:12:51,280
Today we may hide our sin from the eyes of men, but they will be naked before Him.

577
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:55,360
Shall our final appearing bring shame or reward?

578
01:12:56,320 --> 01:13:05,680
Is there a time to be seeking for self-esteem, honor, and recognition when we ought to be seeking only the glory of God?

579
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:09,680
Remember, we are not our own.

580
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:15,520
We have been bought with a price, and our chief end is to glorify God forever.

581
01:13:17,120 --> 01:13:23,520
We move now to the final point this morning, and that is the terrible punishment of Gehazah.

582
01:13:24,160 --> 01:13:26,640
You see, sin must be punished.

583
01:13:27,280 --> 01:13:36,880
In verse 27, Elisha said to Gehazah, The leprosy, therefore, of Naban shall cling unto thee and unto thy seed forever.

584
01:13:37,200 --> 01:13:41,440
And he went out from his presence, a leper, as white as snow.

585
01:13:42,080 --> 01:13:44,640
Oh, the last statement is an ugly one.

586
01:13:45,280 --> 01:13:49,920
He went out from his presence, a leper, as white as snow.

587
01:13:50,320 --> 01:13:53,120
Here, we have a picture of death itself.

588
01:13:53,680 --> 01:14:01,200
Leprosy eats away at the body of man, and infection sets in until finally physical death comes.

589
01:14:02,080 --> 01:14:10,080
And like leprosy, sin eats away at the soul of man until his heart and his life is filled with corruption and wickedness.

590
01:14:10,400 --> 01:14:15,120
The Bible tells us that sin, when it is finished, bringeth forth death.

591
01:14:16,080 --> 01:14:22,880
Jehazah went out from his master's presence, covered with this leather spot of sin.

592
01:14:24,080 --> 01:14:31,920
And his covetousness led him to err from the faith and to pierce himself through with many thoughts.

593
01:14:32,240 --> 01:14:50,000
You recall the words that Apostle Paul so clearly saved him in his first letter to Timothy chapter 6 and verse 10, for the love of money is the root of all evil, which while some coveted after, they have erred from the faith and pierced themselves through with many thoughts.

594
01:14:50,400 --> 01:14:54,160
This was so vividly carried out in the experience of Jehazer.

595
01:14:54,800 --> 01:15:10,160
And as he went out from the presence of the master, not only was the terrible, miserable curse of leprosy placed upon him, but with it there was the sorrow of a personal humiliation and shame.

596
01:15:10,800 --> 01:15:18,480
He was a leper, and to those who came near him, he must cover his mouth and cry, unclean, unclean.

597
01:15:20,640 --> 01:15:26,320
For you see, he was a shameful, disgraced, and outcast in society.

598
01:15:27,600 --> 01:15:29,440
But there was further punishment.

599
01:15:29,760 --> 01:15:33,760
There was the sorrow of being alienated from his master.

600
01:15:34,080 --> 01:15:39,600
He went out from his presence, separated, never to return.

601
01:15:40,160 --> 01:15:42,240
Oh, such punishment indeed.

602
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:47,920
All this, my friend, is a punishment to those who die in their sins.

603
01:15:48,240 --> 01:15:53,760
Eternal alienation from the presence of our Lord and Master Jesus Christ.

604
01:15:54,080 --> 01:15:58,400
Oh, what an awful, what an awful punishment.

605
01:15:59,360 --> 01:16:14,720
But when men refuse God and refuse to take him into their hearts and live for him, their destiny, according to the word of God, will be a time and a day that is forever in punishment, separated from God forever, alienated from him.

606
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:28,960
Finally, there was a third sorrow, and the sorrow of bringing his offspring into the same condemnation.

607
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:36,960
The words of Elisha were, the leprosy of Naaman shall cling unto thee and unto thy seed.

608
01:16:37,760 --> 01:16:40,720
You see, no man liveth unto himself.

609
01:16:41,600 --> 01:16:48,480
Let me tell you folks, that, believe me, our lives touch others.

610
01:16:50,080 --> 01:16:58,240
And here in the case of Gehazah, the weakness and influence of this man would fulfill itself in your children.

611
01:16:59,840 --> 01:17:07,200
How often, dear ones, have you experienced the weak and covetous spirit of Gehazah within your own heart?

612
01:17:09,360 --> 01:17:19,680
Gehazah, having loved this present world and having denied God for dreams of gain, seemed to have become a castaway from disturbing God.

613
01:17:22,080 --> 01:17:23,760
Castaway from disturbing God.

614
01:17:24,560 --> 01:17:25,840
What about your life?

615
01:17:26,400 --> 01:17:30,720
Are you building your future on the gains of this present world?

616
01:17:31,280 --> 01:17:33,920
If so, you are building your castle at the end.

617
01:17:34,480 --> 01:17:41,440
For the Bible says, what shall it profit a man, though he should king the whole world, and yet move his own soul?

618
01:17:42,800 --> 01:17:48,800
And what is a man profited in the end if he lays up treasures on earth and is not rich toward God?

619
01:17:50,400 --> 01:18:00,400
And what shall it profit his children, though if they inherit his earthly riches, they also inherit his earthly spirit?

620
01:18:01,280 --> 01:18:02,400
What about you?

621
01:18:03,920 --> 01:18:05,600
Are you building your castle?

622
01:18:07,120 --> 01:18:09,200
Is your interest only self-interest?

623
01:18:11,440 --> 01:18:27,120
Is your desire in this life to just make a big splash and to be half fame and fortune, to have recognition of others, to cause others to look at you and say, wow, that's a person of power.

624
01:18:30,880 --> 01:18:32,800
That's a person of dignity.

625
01:18:35,920 --> 01:18:37,280
What is our purpose today?

626
01:18:37,440 --> 01:18:44,960
Is it to be sold out to Jesus Christ or is it to fulfill selfish pleasures and self-mint?

